The weapon triangle is a rock-paper-scissors system in Fire Emblem that means that different types of weapons have advantage over others. 
There are technically two triangles, the Weapon Triangle and Trinity of Magic, but the concept as a whole is called the "Weapon Triangle". Bows and Staves are exempt from this system.
Weapon Triangle{br}The weapon triangle between swords/lances/axes has a 3 DMG/15 Hit Advantage/Disadvantage to the weapon with the Advantage/Disadvantage.{br}
Swords beat Axes{br}Axes beat Lances{br}Lances beat Swords
Trinity of Magic{br}The trinity of magic between anima/light/dark also has a 3 DMG/15 Hit Advantage/Disadvantage to the weapon with the Advantage/Disadvantage.{br}
Anima beats Light{br}Light beats Dark{br}Dark beats Anima

Supports work a little differently in this game. Instead of building up points to increase your ranks, support ranks are instead granted by having characters talk during interlude chapters.{br}
Additionally, fielding certain characters in certain chapters and having them talk may also increase support ranks. Be sure to experiment and see who can talk to who per chapter.{br}
Finally, every support offers unique bonuses and penalties instead of set numbers, so try them out.

Name: Letty Whiterock{br}Working Hours: December - February{br}
Letty is a very strange character, scaling off of a weird mix of Mag and Res. Her "Flood of Frost" combat art allows her to slow down enemies and boost her own damage at the same time (indirectly through the Res boost). 
Letty does absolutely wonderfully against magic users, but she might flounder a bit if she's caught on the defense against physical units.

Name: Unknown{br}Nickname: Daiyousei{br}
An unexpectedly strong fairy that lives along Misty Lake's shores. A few villagers have mentioned seeing her playing with the others a few times. Her power is anomalously above average for a fairy. Appears to be a sub-leader amongst the fairies. [Reference Needed.] She seems to share a bond with the ice fairy, although the two have been seen by Marisa Kirisame to have come to blows a few times. Fairies are quite fickle. For categorization purposes, I will title her "Daiyousei", as her power is "bigger" than the average fairy.
Daiyousei builds up Crit very fast using her ability, Nature Power. She should be used with high critical weapons to get the most out of her ability to spam critical hits.
